content:
OmniStudio and OmniStudio for Vlocity differ in a few ways, but the key differences are the data models, the features available in each, and how you access each suite depending on your org licenses. Think of OmniStudio Standard and OmniStudio for Vlocity as two versions of an application suite, not two types of packages.

OmniStudio for Vlocity is the original version of a set of services, components, and data model objects used to create Vlocity Industry Cloud apps by setting up guided interactions using data from your Salesforce org and external sources. Some features in OmniStudio for Vlocity include the original Angular Vlocity Cards and OmniScripts (Angular was supported until December 31, 2022), LWC OmniScripts and LWC FlexCards, Vlocity Interaction Launcher, Omnistudio Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, and Calculation Procedures and Matrices.

OmniStudio Standard uses the standard object model. Some features in OmniStudio include FlexCards, OmniScripts, Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, Business Rules Engine (which replaced Calculation Procedures and Matrices), and Document Generation with a right license.

OmniStudio products use standard objects, which are included with Salesforce by default. OmniStudio for Vlocity products use custom objects, which extend standard functionality and store information thatâ€™s unique to an org.

To view, create, and modify OmniStudio Standard content, your org must have the OmniStudio package installed. To view, create, and modify OmniStudio for Vlocity content, you must have an Industries managed package installed.
title: OmniStudio vs Vlocity: Differences and Features
